summary: An ordinance providing for submission to the qualified electors (voters) of The City of Seattle at a special election to be held therein on November 2, 1965 of a proposition for continuance of the 16 mill property tax levy by and for the benefit of The City of Seattle notwithstanding the limitations of Sections 2, 3 & 4, Chapter 174, Ex. Sess., Laws of 1965; providing for certification of said proposition and prescribing the ballot title.
